Description.SourceString: Here begins the infestation.
From the cocoon-like egg emerges wiry, spindly legs.
Though newly born, it is already prepared to feast.
One day its spiderlings will spill across the realm.
A book published by Pamela Jenkins that may not hold up to fact checks.
"Dr. Gordon, this is your wake-up call."
A ship that carries hope for love.
An intriguing clue, but try not to obsess over it too much.
Sometimes following your heart doesn’t take you where you’d like.
A mask from the Chinese market, it was the first of many used in Jigsaw’s crusade.
"Do you want to play a game?"
To unlock it, ask yourself: What are you willing to do in order to live?
A sweet treat for the one you’d sacrifice yourself for.
What lengths would you go to for love?
The slaughterhouse closed but the killings continued.
"Until you come clean, many more will die."
A pin from Nea’s favorite punk rock band, Slain Riot.
How could you say no to a smile like that?
This combine has harvested more than crops.
Call the crows. The feast is ready.
A jovial puppet that carries a very serious message.
Nea’s kitty, Rotten, dressed in his favorite punk rock outfit.
She would prove herself as the only rightful successor of Jigsaw.
Rotten entrails were poured in the tunnel that collected the Gideon meatpacking plant's wastewater.
Blood dribbled from a brick wall, displaying an elaborate drawing as the key to salvation.
To become Jigsaw's successor, she made her own decisions.
Fueled with adrenaline, she put on the mask once more.
Detective Tapp planned to vacation with his wife, but he couldn't leave now...
From inside the abandoned factory, a scream cried out.
Tapp had little time to react. He chased the cloaked figure.
A bloody game was planned for a young man.
Detective Tapp agonized over the choice he made.
A brave predator with a ferocious bite.
A statuette depicting the third animal of the Chinese zodiac.
